            <!-- ATS Tips -->
            <div class="content-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">
                    <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> ATS-Friendly Resume Tips
                </h2>
                
                <div class="tips-list">
                    <div class="tip-item">
                        <div class="tip-number">1</div>
                        <div class="tip-content">
                            <h4>Use Standard Section Headings</h4>
                            <p>Use common headings like "Work Experience", "Education", "Skills", "Projects". Avoid creative titles that ATS might not recognize.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-item">
                        <div class="tip-number">2</div>
                        <div class="tip-content">
                            <h4>Keyword Optimization</h4>
                            <p>Include keywords from the job description. Match your skills and experience with the exact terms used in the job posting.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-item">
                        <div class="tip-number">3</div>
                        <div class="tip-content">
                            <h4>Simple Formatting</h4>
                            <p>Avoid tables, columns, graphics, and fancy fonts. Use standard fonts (Arial, Calibri, Times New Roman) and clear bullet points.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-item">
                        <div class="tip-number">4</div>
                        <div class="tip-content">
                            <h4>File Format Matters</h4>
                            <p>Always submit your resume as a PDF or Word document (.docx). Avoid JPEG, PNG, or other image formats that ATS can't read.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-item">
                        <div class="tip-number">5</div>
                        <div class="tip-content">
                            <h4>Include Contact Information</h4>
                            <p>Make sure your name, phone number, email, and LinkedIn profile are clearly visible at the top of your resume.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Fresher Resume Guide -->
            <div class="content-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">
                    <i class="fas fa-user-graduate"></i> Fresher Resume Guide
                </h2>
                
                <div class="guide-section">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Essential Sections for Freshers</h3>
                    <p>As a fresher, focus on these sections to showcase your potential:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Objective Statement:</strong> 2-3 lines about your career goals</li>
                        <li><strong>Education:</strong> Include GPA, relevant coursework, achievements</li>
                        <li><strong>Projects:</strong> Academic or personal projects with technologies used</li>
                        <li><strong>Skills:</strong> Technical skills, soft skills, languages</li>
                        <li><strong>Internships/Training:</strong> Any practical experience</li>
                        <li><strong>Certifications:</strong> Relevant online courses or certifications</li>
                        <li><strong>Extracurricular Activities:</strong> Leadership roles, events organized</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="guide-section">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-star"></i> Fresher Resume Tips</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Keep it to 1 page:</strong> Recruiters spend 6-7 seconds on initial screening</li>
                        <li><strong>Quantify achievements:</strong> Instead of "worked on project", say "developed app with 100+ downloads"</li>
                        <li><strong>Use action verbs:</strong> Developed, Managed, Created, Implemented, Optimized</li>
                        <li><strong>Tailor for each job:</strong> Customize your resume for every application</li>
                        <li><strong>Include GitHub/Live Projects:</strong> Show your practical skills</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Common Mistakes -->
            <div class="content-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">
                    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Common Resume Mistakes to Avoid
                </h2>
                
                <div class="questions-list">
                    <div class="question-item">
                        <div class="question-header">
                            <div class="question-icon">
                                <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
                            </div>
                            <h4>Typos and Grammatical Errors</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-content">
                            <p>Spelling mistakes and grammar errors show lack of attention to detail. Always use tools like Grammarly and get someone to proofread.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="question-item">
                        <div class="question-header">
                            <div class="question-icon">
                                <i class="fas fa-clock"></i>
                            </div>
                            <h4>Too Long or Too Short</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-content">
                            <p>Freshers: 1 page, Mid-level: 2 pages, Senior: 2-3 pages max. Remove irrelevant old experiences.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="question-item">
                        <div class="question-header">
                            <div class="question-icon">
                                <i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i>
                            </div>
                            <h4>Generic Objective Statements</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-content">
                            <p>Avoid "seeking challenging position". Instead, mention specific role and how you can contribute to the company.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="question-item">
                        <div class="question-header">
                            <div class="question-icon">
                                <i class="fas fa-list"></i>
                            </div>
                            <h4>Listing Duties Instead of Achievements</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-content">
                            <p>Don't just list job responsibilities. Show what you accomplished with numbers and results.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

